OL,4,CCovid: Train bosses say social
OL,5,Cdistancing not always possible
OL,6, Wales' train operator has been accused
OL,7, of "empty words" after failing to
OL,8, enforce social distancing rules.
OL,10,FArfon MP Hywel Williams said Transport
OL,11,Ffor Wales (TfW) had pledged to make the
OL,12,Fsafety of customers an "absolute
OL,13,Fpriority".
OL,15,FHowever, he said the rail service then
OL,16,Fissued guidance to staff telling them
OL,17,Fnot to enforce social distancing rules.
OL,19,FTfW said that as passenger demand
OL,20,Fincreases, social distancing "will not
OL,21,Falways be possible" during busy times.
